<div id="wb_element_instance828" class="wb_element" style=" line-height: normal;"><h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:#inherit;"><strong>ARGENTINA ADVENTURE</strong></span></h3>

<h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"> </h3>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1"><strong>THIS TIME, YOU WILL ENJOY THE CITY OF BUENOS AIRES AND YOU WILL KNOW THE SECRETS OF THE TANGO. SOAK UP THE EXCITEMENT AND BEAUTY, WITH WATERFALLS OF IGUAZÚ FALLS. YOU WILL BE ABLE TO BE ON FEET OF THE SOUTHERN RIGHT WHALE IN PUERTO MADRYN AND FINALLY YOU WILL STAY FROZEN WHEN CONTEMPLATING THE INCREDIBLE PERITO MORENO GLACIER IN EL CALAFATE. ENJOY IT!</strong></h1>

<p> </p>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1"><strong style='background-color: transparent; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;'><span style="color: rgb(12, 46, 6); font-family: Batang, serif; font-size: 20px; text-align: justify; background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">ARGENTINA ADVENTURE Ciudad de Buenos Aires | Iguazú | Puerto Madryn | ElCalafate </span></strong></h3>

<h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">15 DAYS / 13 NIGHTS</span></strong></h3>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The program includes the following services:</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">* Transfers Airport/ Hotel/ Airport<br>
* 4 nights lodging with breakfast in Buenos Aires.<br>
* 3 nights lodging with breakfast in Iguazú.<br>
* 3 nights lodging with breakfast in Puerto Madryn.<br>
* 3 nights lodging with breakfast in El Calafate.<br>
* Excursions in Buenos Aires: A Tour in Buenos Aires City. Dinner &amp; Tango Show. Two golf day.<br>
* Excursions in Iguazú: Excursion to Iguazú Falls visiting both the Argentinean, and the Brazilian side.<br>
* Excursions in Puerto Madryn: Excursion to Punta Tombo with toninas sightseeing and excursion to Peninsula Valdes<br>
* Excursions in El Calafate: Excursion to Perito Moreno Glacier bridges.<br>
 </span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Not Included:<br>
- Domestic or International flights<br>
- Entrances to National Park</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 1: Europe/America</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">With the Southern Cross Constellation as a guide you fly over the Atlantic Ocean to live an unforgettable experience in Argentina with its incredible scenery and wild nature. Enjoy your quiet flight over the ocean to take a rest, and to prepare for what comes next.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 2: Marvelous Buenos Aires</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The city tour lets you discover the great city located on the De La Plata River. Buenos Aires captures her visitors at first sight, specially with numerous cultural options. “La Reina del Plata” as it was referred to in tangos casts a spell on her guests. Theaters, restaurants, cinemas, bars and coffee shops allow you to discover Buenos Aires´ identity.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 3: Golf day in Buenos Aires</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">After breakfast, you will enjoy a beautiful day of golf. Transfer to Hotel. Lodging.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 4: Buenos Aires / Iguazu</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">In Iguazú, nature offers you a marvelous sight. 900 meters of passages over Rio Iguazú, and the breathtaking Iguazú falls will astonish you.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 5: Iguazú / “Garganta del Diablo” or Throat of the Devil</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">On the “Jungle Train” you begin the ride to the heart of the Iguazú falls. A walk along the passages allows you to walk among the waterfalls till you reach the “Garganta del Diablo”. The possibility of having a baptism by these spraying waters, on a short trip by boat, is an optional excursion very difficult to resist!</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 6: Brazilian falls</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Enjoy the Iguazú falls from the Brazilian side through 900 meters of passages.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 7: Iguazú / Puerto Madryn</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">A very short flight from Iguazú allows you to reach Trelew city, where you begin one of the most surprising adventures: the sightseeing of the Franca Austral Whales in the warm waters of the Golfo Nuevo in front of Puerto Madryn.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 8: Puerto Madryn, adventure in the Peninsula</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">A boat takes you from Puerto Piramides to the blue deep waters of Mar Argentino, where in the between the months of July and December the whales arrive to<br>
procreate and take care of their little offspring</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 9: Puerto Madryn, penguins</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">You can observe the big colony of Magallanes penguins in Puerto Madryn, that flock in the Patagonian coast from October to March these are one of the treasures that you can enjoy in the excursion to Punta Tombo.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 10: Puerto Madryn – El Calafate</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The Glacier air strokes your face softly as soon as you get off the plane coming from Puerto Madryn. You arrive in El Calafate city, the access to the impressing Perito Moreno Glacier.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 11: El Calafate – Perito Moreno Glacier</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">You reach the glacier walking through the passages that let you contemplate the magnificent view of the glacier, it is a soundless white river, with blue tones that<br>
waits patiently to fall into the Argentino lake.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 12: El Calafate - Free day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">This region offers lots of options to enjoy The Glaciers National Park.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 13: El Calafate – Buenos Aires</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">The plane brings you back to Buenos Aires. Our package includes a Dinner &amp;Tango Show at Carlos Gardel Corner to discover the secrets of the most famous Argentine dance.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 14: Buenos Aires, Golf day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">After breakfast, you will enjoy a beautiful day of golf. Transfer to Hotel. Lodging.</span></strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">Day 15: Buenos Aires, last day</span></strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;">All along your trip you have visited the most marvelous regions of this planet. Ezeiza International Airport is your last stop before boarding your international flight. End of our services.</span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="background-color: transparent;"> </span></strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>
